                          "name": "chapH",
                          "fill": "$heading-text",
                          "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                          "width": "fill_container",
                          "content": "Chapter 1: The Ten Sefirot and Their Lights",
                          "fontFamily": "$font-display",
                          "fontSize": 22,
                          "fontWeight": "700"
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "id": "NbVWZ",
                          "name": "para1",
                          "fill": "$body-text",
                          "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                          "width": "fill_container",
                          "content": "Know that before the emanated beings were created, the Simple Infinite Light (Ohr Ein Sof) filled all of existence. There was no vacant space, no empty air, nothing — only the Simple Infinite Light.",
                          "lineHeight": 1.75,
                          "fontFamily": "$font-body",
                          "fontSize": 16,
                          "fontWeight": "normal"
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "id": "gRJF3",
                          "name": "para2",
                          "fill": "$body-text",
                          "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                          "width": "fill_container",
                          "content": "When it arose in the Thought of the Simple Light to create the worlds and emanate the emanations, in order to reveal His perfection to His creations, He then contracted Himself (Tzimtzum) in the point of the center of His light.",
                          "lineHeight": 1.75,
                          "fontFamily": "$font-body",
                          "fontSize": 16,
                          "fontWeight": "normal"
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "frame",
                          "id": "z5tIhP",
                          "name": "para3row",
                          "width": "fill_container",
                          "gap": 10,
                          "children": [
                            {
                              "id": "Zo7Fn",
                              "type": "ref",
                              "ref": "qHnnL",
                              "name": "mb3"
                            },
                            {
                              "type": "text",
                              "id": "HSQmp",
                              "name": "para3txt",
                              "fill": "$body-text",
                              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                              "width": "fill_container",
                              "content": "After the Tzimtzum, a Reshimu (impression) remained — a thin residue of the original light that could not be entirely removed from the vacated space.",
                              "lineHeight": 1.75,
                              "fontFamily": "$font-body",
                              "fontSize": 16,
                              "fontWeight": "normal"
                            }
                          ]
                        },
                        {
                          "id": "FEgLa",
                          "type": "ref",
                          "ref": "sDgyu",
                          "layoutPosition": "absolute",
                          "x": 48,
                          "y": 400,
                          "name": "popover",
                          "descendants": {
                            "o5WF8i": {
                              "content": "Vol. I · Part 1 · Ch. 3"
                            },
                            "lmgpi": {
                              "content": "Definition of Reshimu"
                            },
                            "Lhcw7": {
                              "content": "The Reshimu is the impression left after the Tzimtzum — a thin trace of the Infinite Light that remained within the vacated space."
                            }
                          }
                        }
                      ]
                    }
