                          "content": "This connects to the concept of tzimtzum — the contraction of infinite light that creates space for the worlds.\n\nBaal HaSulam explains that this is not a physical contraction but a restriction of the will to receive. The Kli (vessel) reduced its desire so that the Ohr (light) could be received in a more structured way.\n\nSee also: Introduction to TES, §12 — where he discusses the relationship between the contraction and the subsequent emanation of the line (Kav).",
