                              "width": "fill_container",
                              "content": "Chapter 1: The Ten Sefirot and Their Lights",
                              "fontFamily": "$font-display",
                              "fontSize": 22,
                              "fontWeight": "600"
                            },
                            {
                              "type": "text",
                              "id": "sKEz5",
                              "name": "dmPara1",
                              "fill": "#b0a898",
                              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                              "width": "fill_container",
                              "content": "Know that before the emanated beings were created, the Simple Infinite Light (Ohr Ein Sof) filled all of existence. There was no vacant space, no empty air, nothing — only the Simple Infinite Light.",
                              "fontFamily": "$font-body",
                              "fontSize": 16,
                              "fontWeight": "normal"
                            },
                            {
                              "type": "text",
                              "id": "OwPtk",
                              "name": "dmPara2",
                              "fill": "#b0a898",
                              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                              "width": "fill_container",
                              "content": "When it arose in the Thought of the Simple Light to create the worlds and emanate the emanations, He contracted Himself (Tzimtzum) in the point of the center of His light.",
                              "fontFamily": "$font-body",
                              "fontSize": 16,
                              "fontWeight": "normal"
                            },
                            {
                              "type": "text",
                              "id": "T3RRv",
                              "name": "dmPara3",
                              "fill": "#b0a898",
                              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                              "width": "fill_container",
                              "content": "After the Tzimtzum, a Reshimu (impression) remained — a thin residue of the original light that could not be entirely removed from the vacated space.",
                              "fontFamily": "$font-body",
                              "fontSize": 16,
                              "fontWeight": "normal"
                            }
                          ]
                        }
