                      "content": "A Student of the Tradition",
                      "fontFamily": "$font-display",
                      "fontSize": 24,
                      "fontWeight": "600"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "bzxkF",
                      "name": "abBioP1",
                      "fill": "$body-text",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "Dr. Michael Laitman is the founder and director of Bnei Baruch Kabbalah Academy. From 1979 until 1991, he was a personal student of Rabbi Baruch Shalom HaLevi Ashlag, the firstborn son and successor of Rabbi Yehuda Leib HaLevi Ashlag — Baal HaSulam.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.7,
                      "fontFamily": "$font-body",
                      "fontSize": 15,
                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "GWBnf",
                      "name": "abBioP2",
                      "fill": "$body-text",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "Following the passing of his teacher, Dr. Laitman established Bnei Baruch to continue the work of disseminating the wisdom of Kabbalah to all who seek it. He holds a PhD in Philosophy and Kabbalah from the Moscow Institute of Philosophy of the Russian Academy of Sciences and an MS in Bio-Cybernetics from St. Petersburg State Polytechnic University.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.7,
                      "fontFamily": "$font-body",
                      "fontSize": 15,
                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "Ua1Au",
                      "name": "abBioP3",
                      "fill": "$body-text",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "He has authored more than 40 books on Kabbalah, translated to over 30 languages, including modern commentaries on Talmud Eser Sefirot, The Book of Zohar, and Baal HaSulam's writings on the structure of the worlds.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.7,
                      "fontFamily": "$font-body",
                      "fontSize": 15,
                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
